    "content": "<p>Selected data points of the step response of a stable first-order linear time-invariant (LTI) system are given below. The closest value of the time-constant, in sec, of the system is</p>\n$$\n\\begin{array}{|l|c|c|c|c|c|}\n\\hline \\text { Time (sec) } & 0.6 & 1.6 & 2.6 & 10 & \\infty \\\\\n\\hline \\text { Output } & 0.78 & 1.65 & 2.18 & 2.98 & 3 \\\\\n\\hline\n\\end{array}\n$$",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "1"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "2"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "3"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "4"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>A first-order step response has the form  </p>\n<p>$$y(t)=K\\bigl(1-e^{-t/τ}\\bigr)$$  </p>\n<p>Here the final value is $K=3$. So at time $t$,  </p>\n<p>$$e^{-t/τ}=1-\\frac{y(t)}{3}\\,. $$  </p>\n<p>Let’s pick the data point at $t=0.6$ s, $y=0.78$:  </p>\n\n<p><p>Compute the exponential term:  </p>\n<p>$$e^{-0.6/τ}=1-\\frac{0.78}{3}=0.74\\,. $$</p></p>\n<p><p>Take logarithms:  </p>\n<p>$$-0.6/τ=\\ln(0.74)\\approx-0.3011$$  </p></p>\n<p><p>Solve for $τ$:  </p>\n<p>$$τ=-\\frac{0.6}{\\ln(0.74)}\\approx\\frac{0.6}{0.3011}\\approx2.0\\ {\\rm s}$$  </p></p>\n\n<p>Checking the other points (e.g. $t=1.6$, $y=1.65$ or $t=2.6$, $y=2.18$) gives the same result, $τ\\approx2$ s.  </p>\n<p>Answer: Option B) 2 sec.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2025",
    "difficulty": null
  },
