    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Consider a closed loop system as shown.</p>\n<p>$$ G_p(s)=\\frac{14.4}{s(1+0.1 s)} $$</p>\n<p>is the plant transfer function and $G_c(s)=1$ is the compensator. For a unit-step input, the output response has damped oscillations. The damped natural frequency is $\\_\\_\\_\\_$ $\\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$. (Round off to 2 decimal places).</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh61qyaw/1791f114-53d0-4592-a1dd-80b226a2cbf7/9f99ea80-b180-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh61qyax.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh61qyaw/1791f114-53d0-4592-a1dd-80b226a2cbf7/9f99ea80-b180-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh61qyax.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Control Systems - Time Response Analysis Question 1 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "10.90",
    "explanation": "<p>Given : $G_p(s)=\\frac{14.4}{s(1+0.1 s)}$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} G_p(s) & =\\frac{14.4}{0.1 s(s+10)} \\\\ G_p(s) & =\\frac{144}{s(s+10)} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>and&nbsp;&nbsp;$$ G_c(s)=1 $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\therefore \\quad G_p(s)_{C L T F}=\\frac{144}{s^2+10 s+144} \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(i)$$</p>\n<p>Now, comparing with the standard equation,</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow \\quad \\frac{\\omega_n^2}{s^2+2 \\xi \\omega_n s+\\omega_n^2} \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(ii)$$</p>\n<p>From equation (i) and (ii),</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} & \\omega_n=12 \\\\ & 2 \\xi \\omega_n=10 \\\\ & \\xi=\\frac{10}{2 \\times 12}=\\frac{5}{12} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}Now,\\,\\,\\, & \\omega_d=\\omega_n \\sqrt{1-\\xi^2} \\\\ & \\omega_d=12 \\sqrt{1-\\left(\\frac{5}{12}\\right)^2}=12 \\sqrt{\\frac{144-25}{144}} \\\\ & \\omega_d=12 \\sqrt{\\frac{119}{144}}=10.90 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct answer is 10.90 .</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2021,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2021",
    "difficulty": null
  },
